Real-Time Bayesian Spam Detector
A Flask-Based Text Classification Engine
This repository contains a professional-grade Spam Filtering system built using a custom Naïve Bayes engine. The project demonstrates the transition from raw, unstructured text to precise probabilistic classification.

Project Overview
Developed as a Computer Science Engineering mini-project, this application uses the UCI SMS Spam Collection (5,572 messages) to identify spam signatures in real-time.

Key Technical Features
Custom Inference Engine: Implemented entirely from scratch in Python to handle Bayesian probability without high-level ML libraries.

Numerical Stability: Utilizes Log-Space Summation to prevent floating-point underflow during high-volume probability calculations.

Laplace Smoothing: Ensures the model handles previously unseen words without resulting in zero-probability errors.

Unbiased Prior: Configured with an unbiased 0.5 prior to ensure fair classification of incoming messages.

Transparent Logic: Features a "Show Math" Panel that breaks down the tokenization, per-word likelihoods, and final posterior calculation for the user.

Tech Stack
Backend: Python 3.10, Flask

Environment: VS Code

Dataset: UCI Machine Learning Repository (SMS Spam Collection v.1)

Frontend: Blackboard-themed HTML/CSS

Performance
Accuracy: 95.52%

Dataset Size: 5,572 Messages

Preprocessing: Tokenization, Lower-casing, Special Character Removal (Bag-of-Words).

Installation & Usage
Clone the Repo:

Bash
git clone https://github.com/MeghaZachariah/Bayesian-Spam-Detector-Flask.git
Install Requirements:

Bash
pip install flask pandas
Run the Server:

Bash
python app.py
Test the App: Visit http://127.0.0.1:5000 and enter messages like "Claim your prize now!" or "Meeting at 3 PM" to see the Bayesian logic in action.
